ments":[{"type":"text","text":"It should work for unary and n-ary ones as well"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"6cdd30e3-7081-490b-8078-6ac08484fb4d","type":"message","text":"but only operators anyway?","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616718769.180000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Bt=b","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"but only operators anyway?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"13846276-9ef0-4a0b-af9e-37784669533b","type":"message","text":"so if one wants to apply a function without an associated operator, they need to define an operator alias?","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616718786.180200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"pWp9","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"so if one wants to apply a function without an associated operator, they need to define an operator alias?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"12582ae4-46ff-4e55-9cca-8e3ed732f2a0","type":"message","text":"Yes, it wouldn't be too hard to add syntax to do this for functions as well, but standalone `f.` just seemed a little bit awkward","user":"UM30MT6RF","ts":"1616718842.180400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"puRbJ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, it wouldn't be too hard to add syntax to do this for functions as well, but standalone "},{"type":"text","text":"f.","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" just seemed a little bit awkward"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"b0d019ea-608b-456b-9cb4-3f3b62fc505c","type":"message","text":"And I guess `.f` is standalone, but too non-standard?","user":"U01FKQQ7J0J","ts":"1616719067.180600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"znx","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"And I guess "},{"type":"text","text":".f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is standalone, but too non-standard?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"e673b251-663d-4e9a-a546-50968ff0cc79","type":"message","text":"dot goes after function name, not before","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616719104.180800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"HDTU","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"dot goes after function name, not before"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"7ac875cc-7b06-4191-a570-9a76b2cd5917","type":"message","text":"`.f` is only valid syntax if `f` is an operator, otherwise it is a syntax error","user":"UM30MT6RF","ts":"1616719135.181000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"fSZ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":".f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is only valid syntax if "},{"type":"text","text":"f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is an operator, otherwise it is a syntax error"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"2b3157e6-4d32-4931-b218-b92365ab7ac8","type":"message","text":"Yeah, but standalone `.f` could, in theory, be a special case for `f.` (but now that I think about it more it doesn't have any benefit over `f.`).  They both look funny! :sweat_smile:","user":"U01FKQQ7J0J","ts":"1616719293.181200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"nZPCF","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, but standalone "},{"type":"text","text":".f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" could, in theory, be a special case for "},{"type":"text","text":"f.","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" (but now that I think about it more it doesn't have any benefit over "},{"type":"text","text":"f.","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":").  They both look funny! "},{"type":"emoji","name":"sweat_smile"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"51414a14-19ac-4eb4-ac64-9f473d6a23bd","type":"message","text":"`f.` could be easily confused with unfinished `getfield`/`getproperty`","user":"UH24GRBLL","ts":"1616744150.186300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Fn8O","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"f.","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" could be easily confused with unfinished "},{"type":"text","text":"getfield","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"/"},{"type":"text","text":"getproperty","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"995f199c-f93a-4cf5-9ce4-e6dc63cbb00c","type":"message","text":"`.f`  makes some sense. An operator used like a function uses a post-fix dot too. Just that functions can't be written like operators.\n\n```(+).([1,3],[5,6])\nmap(.+, [[1,3],4], [[5,6],5])```","user":"U01HD5VFXJM","ts":"1616772777.222700","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"U01HD5VFXJM","ts":"1616773029.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"4qm4O","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":".f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"  makes some sense. An operator used like a function uses a post-fix dot too. Just that functions can't be written like operators.\n\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(+).([1,3],[5,6])\nmap(.+, [[1,3],4], [[5,6],5])"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"73e1082b-cd8c-42fe-a8aa-63b696f413ff","type":"message","text":"I find it weird that the dot would be sometimes postfix and sometimes prefix for functions","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616773042.223400","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616773054.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"b9al4","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I find it weird that the dot would be sometimes postfix and sometimes prefix for functions"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"98a06efb-931c-4988-81a9-1bf9edceddac","type":"message","text":"We already make that distinction, i.e. you write `.+(a, b)`, but `f.(a, b)`","user":"UM30MT6RF","ts":"1616774477.231600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"3njem","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We already make that distinction, i.e. you write "},{"type":"text","text":".+(a, b)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":", but "},{"type":"text","text":"f.(a, b)","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"d6c13bc3-29dd-4337-9b12-7593a75bc71d","type":"message","text":"yes, but one is an operator and the other is a function.  I specified \"function\" above for a reason :slightly_smiling_face:","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616774513.232100","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"dGPl","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"yes, but one is an operator and the other is a function.  I specified \"function\" above for a reason "},{"type":"emoji","name":"slightly_smiling_face"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"5ad539d3-d677-4738-bdc7-aab8aaf593d5","type":"message","text":"OK, sorry, I think I was just confused:see_no_evil:","user":"UM30MT6RF","ts":"1616774580.232600","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"0AjO","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, sorry, I think I was just confused"},{"type":"emoji","name":"see_no_evil"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"3420d9c4-bced-4f64-ace0-1396d841f894","type":"message","text":"I do think it's very slightly confusing the difference between operators and functions, but at least it's consistent: operators -&gt; always prefix, functions -&gt; always postfix","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616774644.233100","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qL8","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I do think it's very slightly confusing the difference between operators and functions, but at least it's consistent: operators -> always prefix, functions -> always postfix"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"1a4d2ebf-35fa-4759-8d87-46623372cb69","type":"message","text":"but having for functions sometimes prefix and sometimes postfix is just a recipe for disaster for newcomers","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616774688.233400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"F+So0","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"but having for functions sometimes prefix and sometimes postfix is just a recipe for disaster for newcomers"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"223fc39e-6822-44aa-8317-e95db5a7bc20","type":"message","text":"Yes, that I agree with","user":"UM30MT6RF","ts":"1616774751.233800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"AwsIy","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, that I agree with"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"},{"client_msg_id":"80f87c4b-eaa9-44fd-b37f-6bff90080ef7","type":"message","text":"It seems like the `.+` in `map(.+, a, b)` is just shorthand for `Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(+)`.  Maybe `.foo` could be treated as shorthand for `Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(foo)`, which can be used right now to get the desired functionality, but it's very verbose:\n```julia&gt; f(a, b) = a ⊻ b\nf (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia&gt; map(Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(f), [1, 2, 3], [13, 14, 15])\n3-element Vector{Int64}:\n 12\n 12\n 12```\nI guess I'm going back to liking this `.f` idea after all (plus it would drive OO people crazy :stuck_out_tongue: )","user":"U01FKQQ7J0J","ts":"1616778670.248200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"=hNME","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"It seems like the "},{"type":"text","text":".+","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"text","text":"map(.+, a, b)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is just shorthand for "},{"type":"text","text":"Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(+)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":".  Maybe "},{"type":"text","text":".foo","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" could be treated as shorthand for "},{"type":"text","text":"Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(foo)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":", which can be used right now to get the desired functionality, but it's very verbose:\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> f(a, b) = a ⊻ b\nf (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia> map(Broadcast.BroadcastFunction(f), [1, 2, 3], [13, 14, 15])\n3-element Vector{Int64}:\n 12\n 12\n 12"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"I guess I'm going back to liking this `.f` idea after all (plus it would drive OO people crazy "},{"type":"emoji","name":"stuck_out_tongue"},{"type":"text","text":" )"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616717024.176300","parent_user_id":"U9RDM8ZGT"}]